The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, January 15, 2004 				 Its Spring time, thanks to Christian Dior 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								New Delhi, Jan. 14: Christian Dior today launched its latest international Spring 2004 watch range  Dior Girly in India. This premium upmarket womens brand is priced between Rs 30,500 to Rs 44,000. 																								We are very pleased that the Indian consumer is ready to appreciate these international trends, said Valerie Lachaux, CEO, Christian Dior Watches, who was here for the launch. 																								Initially, the watch will be available in about 25 retail outlets in the four metro cities of Delhi, Calcutta, Mumbai and Chennai. The national roll out, which will see an expansion to retail outlets in another 13-14 cities, will be completed within a week. 																								Christian Dior entered the Indian market two years back. It is a pre-dominantly womens watch brand though it also has mens range. The other brand that LVMH watches have is TAG Heuer. 																								Christian Dior watches are a part of LVMH Watches amp; Jewellery, the worlds leading luxury group. Dior watches are distributed in over 150 countries at 1,500 carefully selected sales outlets and 115 Christian Dior boutiques. In India, Dior watches are available at 31 retail points in across 13 cities.																								The company is reluctant to disclose its sales figures in India but maintained that the company has been growing at a rate of 20 to 30 per cent, on a month-to-month basis.																								Christian Dior watches and accessories have been very well received by the Indian market. The Indian consumer is informed and savvy to international trends and very closely follows international fashion, said Ravi Thakran, regional managing director, LVMH Watches Asia-Pacific. 
